      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "bc473c57fbaf4608",
      "text": "The documentary explores the question of why it is so difficult to bring aggressors and their wars of aggression before the International Criminal Court (ICC) in The Hague. In March 2023, the ICC issued an arrest warrant for Russia's President Vladimir Putin. The accusation: the abduction of Ukrainian children. With regard to the attack by Ukraine, the ICC has no case against Putin as, according to its statutes, the ICC can only investigate if the aggressor, in this case Russia, has given its consent.\nOn October 7, 2023, Hamas carries out a cruel massacre of Israeli civilians. Israel responds with the largest offensive on Gaza ever. The war threatens to escalate. ICC Chief Prosecutor Karim Khan travels to the Middle East and announces that he will prosecute all kinds of war crimes on both sides."
